ENTRY       EC 4.1.3.24                 Enzyme
NAME        malyl-CoA lyase;
            malyl-coenzyme A lyase;
            (3S)-3-carboxy-3-hydroxypropanoyl-CoA glyoxylate-lyase;
            mclA (gene name);
            mcl1 (gene name);
            (3S)-3-carboxy-3-hydroxypropanoyl-CoA glyoxylate-lyase (acetyl-CoA-forming);
            L-malyl-CoA lyase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-carbon lyases;
            Oxo-acid-lyases
SYSNAME     (S)-malyl-CoA glyoxylate-lyase (acetyl-CoA-forming)
REACTION    (1) (S)-malyl-CoA = acetyl-CoA + glyoxylate [RN:R00473];
            (2) (2R,3S)-2-methylmalyl-CoA = propanoyl-CoA + glyoxylate [RN:R00934]
ALL_REAC    R00473 R00934;
            (other) R00237
SUBSTRATE   (S)-malyl-CoA [CPD:C04348];
            (2R,3S)-2-methylmalyl-CoA [CPD:C06027]
PRODUCT     acetyl-CoA [CPD:C00024];
            glyoxylate [CPD:C00048];
            propanoyl-CoA [CPD:C00100]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the bacterium Chloroflexus aurantiacus, which participates in the 3-hydroxypropanoate cycle for carbon assimilation, also has the activity of EC 4.1.3.25, (3S)-citramalyl-CoA lyase [2,4]. The enzymes from Rhodobacter species are part of acetate assimilation pathways [3,5]. The reactions are reversible.
HISTORY     EC 4.1.3.24 created 1972, modified 2014
